    - "struct_extra98.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct.size/__format__ getset_descriptor class names and qualnames / Struct.size/__format__ qualname/name lengths and __objclass__.__name__ / Struct.__doc__ length (40) and equality (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra97.zspec.zsdl — covers struct module __spec__/__loader__ attribute lengths / Struct/__module__/__len__()==7 / error/__module__/__len__()==6 (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra96.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct method __name__.__len__() / module-level function __name__.__len__() / Struct.__name__/__len__() and error.__name__/__len__() (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra95.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack __qualname__.__len__() / Struct.__qualname__.__len__()==6 / error.__qualname__.__len__()==5 / module-level function __module__.__eq__('_struct') (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra94.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct method __qualname__.__len__() (pack/unpack/pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack) / struct.error.__mro__.__len__()==4 / error MRO entry names (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra93.zspec.zsdl — covers Struct.pack/unpack/pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack __name__ equality / Struct.format/__qualname__ / error/__bases__[0]/__module__ / Struct/__module__/__qualname__/__bases__[0]/__name__ / Struct/__mro__/__len__()==2 (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra92.zspec.zsdl — covers struct module-level function __class__.__name__ / Struct method __class__.__name__ / struct.error inheritance and __module__/__qualname__ / Struct method __qualname__ cross-check (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra91.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.calcsize return values / struct.pack/__qualname__ / struct.Struct.__doc__/__class__.__name__ / struct.error/__class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra90.zspec.zsdl — covers struct module-level function __qualname__ / Struct method __qualname__ equality / Struct method class names (table + invariants)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in earlier struct specs."
    - "Wave 272 theme: struct.Struct method __doc__ string lengths — pack/unpack/pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack method docstring lengths and __doc__ class names."
    - "struct.Struct.pack.__doc__.__len__() == 175. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.unpack.__doc__.__len__() == 190. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.pack_into.__doc__.__len__() == 277. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.unpack_from.__doc__.__len__() == 243. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.iter_unpack.__doc__.__len__() == 196. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.pack.__doc__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.unpack.__doc__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.pack_into.__doc__.__class__.__name__ == 'str'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: These are C-level method_descriptor docstrings from _struct.c, not module-level function docstrings. The module-level function docstrings (pack/unpack/calcsize/pack_into/unpack_from/iter_unpack) were anchored in extra99. The Struct method docstrings are distinct (shorter for pack/unpack/calcsize because they include the 'S.pack(v1, v2, ...)' signature prefix)."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.pack.__doc__ (175 chars) differs from struct.pack.__doc__ (176 chars) anchored in extra99: the module-level pack docstring has one extra character."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.pack_into.__doc__ (277 chars) differs from struct.pack_into.__doc__ (274 chars) anchored in extra99."
